@NODE "what" "Was ist Icons.reko?"
@NEXT "produce"
@PREV "main"
@TOC "MAIN"
 1.1. What is it?
 
 @{fg shine}ICONS.REKO@{fg text} is a cardset
 for Klondike from REKO-PRODUCTIONS.

 As you can imagine my cardset consists of cards 
 with pictures of Workbench-Icons (and not pets or so).

 It a cardset with 59 pictures in 256 colors.


@ENDNODE

@NODE "produce" "Wie wurde Icons.reko erstellt?"
@NEXT "requirements"
@PREV "what"
@TOC "MAIN"
 1.2. How did I produce it?

First I put about 60icons (I made them all!)
in a Workbench-Window.

Than I grabed it and load it in a Paint-Programm.

There I sized the icons up because the cards have
to be 88 x 130 pixels big.

Next I put them on a Workbench-Background-Pattern
and together with the card-symbols.

The four cards in the lower right edge
(where you see a Workbench-Screen)
are made from @{u}my@{uu} Workbench-Screen).

Finally I used a Programm from REKO-Prod. to
made the #?.reko file.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "requirements" "Was braucht man für Icons.reko?"
@NEXT "install"
@PREV "produce"
@TOC "MAIN"
1.3. Requirements

First you need an AMIGA 
(min.1200 with 2MB RAM).

Secoundly the Game Klondike II or better
(I tried my cardset in Version I and it does not work).


@ENDNODE

@NODE "install" "Wie wird Icons.reko installiert?"
@NEXT "usage"
@PREV "requirements"
@TOC "MAIN"
 1.4. Installation

If you do not have Klondike II or better you have to get it and to install.

Copy the #?.reko file to your cards directory.

Change your REKO-Prefs.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "usage" "Wie benutzt man Icons.reko?"
@NEXT "author"
@PREV "install"
@TOC "MAIN"
1.5. Usage

If you have installed it you only have to start Klondike
and to select my cardset.

Now you can play.
(I hope (or I know) you will have much fun with my cardset!!!)

@ENDNODE

